&lt;h2&gt;


Under the Hood
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This isn't a quick hack. The SDK is production-grade:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Typed responses&lt;/strong&gt; — full type hints, IDE autocompletion works everywhere&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Sync + Async&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;client.generate()&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;await client.agenerate()&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Auto-retry&lt;/strong&gt; — exponential backoff on 5xx errors, respects rate limits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Zero dependencies&lt;/strong&gt; — just Python's stdlib HTTP + JSON&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Streaming first-class&lt;/strong&gt; — context managers, not callbacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

